Class:
A class is a blueprint used to create objects.

Object:
An object is an instance of a class.

Encapsulation:
Wrapping data and methods together and restricting direct access using access modifiers.

Inheritance:
When a class derives properties and methods from another class (parent â†’ child).

Polymorphism:
The ability of an object to take many forms (method overloading & overriding).

Abstraction:
Hiding implementation details and showing only essential features.

Interface:
A contract defining methods that a class must implement.
